The Lark OpenAPI MCP is an official tool that enables AI agents to connect to the Feishu/Lark platform, providing access to APIs for messaging, documents, calendar management, and more [1][2]. You can configure it by adding the following to your MCP client configuration [1][3]:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "lark-mcp": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": [
        "-y",
        "@larksuiteoapi/lark-mcp",
        "mcp",
        "-a", "<your_app_id>",
        "-s", "<your_app_secret>"
      ]
    }
  }
}
```

The tool supports stdio and HTTP/SSE modes [4]. You can filter available tools or enable specific presets using the -t parameter [1][3]. Detailed tool naming follows the `biz.version.resource.method` convention, which you can verify via the "Try it out" feature in the Lark Open Platform API documentation [2][5]. Community alternatives like Lark Master MCP also exist to provide broader tool coverage [6].
